<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CLXXXVIII. Agni.</h3>  
<p>1. Now send ye J&#257;tavedas forth, send hitherward the vigorous Steed<br> To seat him on our sacred grass.<br> 2. I raise the lofty eulogy of J&#257;tavedas, raining boons,<br> With sages for his hero band.<br> 3 With flames of J&#257;tavedas which carry oblation to the Gods,<br> May he promote our sacrifice.</p>  
